This paper discusses the ATM Guaranteed Frame Rate (GFR) service and its use for transporting TCP/IP connections over a single VC. This topic is related to network protocols and communication (cs.NI), as well as network security (cs.CR) and data centers (cs.DC). The paper also discusses buffer management and rate control, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM).
